Wait, how did you make the comments pages the same on all of these? @_@

Okay, well, after getting to the end, I have to say, I am incredibly disappointed. Here's my train of thought:

Iteration 0: Oh boy here we go time for another one of these it looks stupid.

Iteration 1: Well, it's cute.

Iteration 2: Still just getting deeper into the rabbit hole, but at least it's written well. I suspect the next one will be Keter and the 'real' one Thaumiel.

Iteration 3: Holy shit this is awesome. Infovores and Foundation departments turning against themselves and each other? Sign me up! The next one's gonna be sweet! I can't wait to piece this together!

Which brings us to iteration 4. Now don't get me wrong, the story of Michelle Yu is really compelling and preventing me from downvoting. I love that collapsible, which I think is a pretty solid callback to that deleted article, and it is a story, which so often gets overlooked in articles. But I can't see the whole  thing as incredibly silly. It's an anime plot. It's just an incredible letdown after all that buildup, and I'm not sure I can adequately articulate why. :(







